ict read/write to owner only\",\n    \"HIGH: Wrap int(os.getenv('SMTP_PORT', '587')) with try-except ValueError and validate port range (1-65535)\",\n    \"HIGH: Add URL validation utility to sanitize webhook/callback URLs; use urllib.parse.urlparse to validate scheme and hostname\",\n    \"MEDIUM: Refactor notify.py error handling - split exception catching by notification type with specific error types\",\n    \"MEDIUM: Consider rotating sensitive identifiers (Twilio SID, Meta doc_id) into a secrets manager rather than hard-coding or environment variables\",\n    \"MEDIUM: Use tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile() instead of predictable temp file names in agent.py:232\",\n    \"MEDIUM: Add HTML escaping for job data fields if ever used in HTML email templates (use html.escape or bleach)\",\n    \"LOW: Add logging with DEBUG-level details to understand which notifications fail (but not secrets)\",\n    \"LOW: Document Meta GraphQL doc_id rotation pattern and add monitoring/alerting for graphql errors\",\n    \"RECOMMENDED: Enable HTTPS verification explicitly: httpx.AsyncClient(..., verify=True) to catch any future ca-bundle issues\",\n    \"RECOMMENDED: Review environment variable handling - consider using python-dotenv with .env.example checking instead of undocumented os.getenv()\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n**Risk Score: 62/100 (Moderate-High Risk)**\n\nThis application is a backend job fetching service with moderate security concerns:\n\n### Key Findings:\n- **No hardcoded API keys or secrets** ✅ (properly using environment variables)\n- **No SQL injection risks** ✅ (all queries use parameterized statements)\n- **No XSS vulnerabilities** ✅ (backend-only, no rendered user input)\n- **SSRF risk** ⚠️ (webhook URL not validated)\n- **TLS/SSL misconfiguration** ⚠️ (SMTP certificate verification missing)\n- **Weak error handling** ⚠️ (could leak sensitive info via exceptions)\n\n### Priority Fixes:\n1. **SMTP TLS verification** - Use ssl.create_default_context()\n2. **We